    Create missing data

    Source: R/missing.R
    ch_missing.Rd

    Create missing data

    Usage

    ch_missing(x, n = 1)

    Arguments

    x

    Input vector, can be any class - only 1 vetor

    n

    (integer) number of things to get, any non-negative integer

    See also

    MissingDataProvider

    Examples

    ch_missing(letters)
#>  [1] NA  NA  "c" NA  "e" "f" NA  "h" NA  "j" "k" NA  "m" NA  "o" "p" "q" NA  "s"
#> [20] "t" NA  NA  NA  "x" NA  NA 
ch_missing(letters, 10)
